    <sys:String x:Key="LOCSsvUsedFilePattern">Used a file pattern</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCSsvUsedFilePatternTooltip" xml:space="preserve">You can directly use a regex pattern or use a simplified version.

To use the simplified version, replace the numbers with {digit} and remove the extension.

Example:
GameName_20200107-1 => GameName_{digit} - {digit}</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCSsvUsedFileSavePatternTooltip" xml:space="preserve">Special variables can be used to add a dynamic string:
{ImagePath} - Game ISO/ROM path if set
{ImageName} - Game ISO/ROM file name
{ImageNameNoExt} - Game ISO/ROM file name without extension
{Name} - Game name
        
{digit} - Incremented file number
{DateModified} - File date modified         
{DateTimeModified} - File date and time modified         
       
Steam variables can be used to add a dynamic string:        
{SteamId} - Steam user Id
        
Windows variables can be used to add a dynamic string:        
{WinDir}
{AllUsersProfile}
{AppData}
{HomePath}
{UserName}
{ComputerName}
{UserProfile}
{HomeDrive}
{SystemDrive}
{SystemRoot}
{Public}
{CommonProgramW6432}
{CommonProgramFiles}
{ProgramFiles}
{CommonProgramFiles(x86)}
{ProgramFiles(x86)}</sys:String>

    <sys:String x:Key="LOCSsvEnableFolderToSave">Enable move of screenshots in unique folder</sys:String>
    <sys:String x:Key="LOCSsvFilePattern">File pattern</sys:String>

